articles.author: FATIMA HUSSEIN and LORNE COOK
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — The United States and the European Union are piling new sanctions on Russia on the eve of the second anniversary of its invasion of Ukraine and in retaliation for the death of noted Kremlin critic Alexei Navalny last week in an Arctic penal colony.
articles.title: US and EU pile new sanctions on Russia for the Ukraine war's 2nd anniversary and Navalny's death

articles.author: The Associated Press
articles.description: An ally of the late opposition leader Alexei Navalny said Friday that Russian authorities have given his mother a deadline to agree to forgo a public funeral or else they’ll bury him on prison grounds.
articles.title: Ally of late Kremlin critic Navalny says authorities threaten to bury him on prison grounds

articles.author: WAFAA SHURAFA and BASSEM MROUE
articles.description: DEIR AL-BALAH, Gaza Strip (AP) — Israel seeks open-ended control over security and civilian affairs in the Gaza Strip, according to a long-awaited postwar plan by Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu. It was swiftly rejected Friday by Palestinian leaders and runs counter to Washington's vision for the war-ravaged enclave.
articles.title: Netanyahu seeks open-ended control over security and civilian affairs in Gaza in new postwar plan

articles.author: PETER SMITH and TIFFANY STANLEY
articles.description: When the Alabama Supreme Court ruled that frozen embryos are considered children under state law, its chief justice had a higher authority in mind.
articles.title: Bible-quoting Alabama chief justice sparks church-state debate in embryo ruling

articles.author: MARCIA DUNN
articles.description: CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) — The moon’s newest arrival was said to be “alive and well” a day after making the first U.S.
articles.title: Lander 'alive and well' after company scores first US moon landing since Apollo era

articles.author: LINDSAY WHITEHURST, RIO YAMAT and KEN RITTER
articles.description: LAS VEGAS (AP) — A former FBI informant who claims to have links to Russian intelligence and is charged with lying about a multimillion-dollar bribery scheme involving President Joe Biden's family was again taken into custody Thursday in Las Vegas, two days after a judge released him.
articles.title: Ex-FBI source accused of lying about Bidens and having Russian contacts is returned to US custody

articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Former President Donald Trump urged a Florida judge to dismiss the criminal case charging him with illegally retaining classified documents, claiming in part that presidential immunity protects him from prosecution even as that sweeping argument has so far in failed in federal appeals courts in a separate case.
articles.title: Trump's lawyers call for dismissal of classified documents case, citing presidential immunity

articles.description: ATHENS, Ga. (AP) — A woman found dead on the University of Georgia campus was a student at a nearby nursing school, said authorities, who were checking security cameras and advising students to travel in groups and avoid the wooded area where her body was found.
articles.title: A woman was found dead on the University of Georgia campus after she failed to return from a run

articles.author: MARY CLARE JALONICK
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer is in Ukraine to try to reassure President Volodymyr Zelenskyy and other officials that Congress will deliver another round of U.S. aid, even as a package that would provide $60 billion is stalled in the U.S.
articles.title: Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer is in Ukraine to meet Zelenskyy as US aid hangs in the balance

articles.author: MARCIA DUNN
articles.description: The complete shrouding of our sun by the moon has mesmerized humanity for millennia — a moment in time when skies darken and stillness creeps in.
articles.title: AP PHOTOS: Total solar eclipses through the decades
